Hello, human. We are the Mush Superiority

We have been watching you. Your struggles in dead ships; the campaigns against the clueless yet willful; your inquisitive, calculating nature, all of these things have caught our eye. You will not prevail alone against the listless masses of the raw community forever. All your misery is unnecessary.

We of the Mush Superiority are a collective of players who utilize Group Jumping methods and Castings to create ships that are more challenging, active and intelligent. We believe in the thrill of the hunt. We believe in stalking observational deduction and manipulation.

If you consider yourself a serious opponent,
If you are prepared for the long campaigns,
If you are willing to live by our rules,
The Mush Superiority can deliver you from suffering.

Join us. You have nowhere to hide. We are everywhere.
About us & ApplicationMS was a jumpgroup created in the pre-castings age so we have an solid community established even before the update! New members are welcome but those applying to join will have their games history checked. We're looking to build a group focused on solid PvP and there are certain mush tactics (or lack of) we frown upon. No RP skill necessary but it is a bonus, we're more oriented on in-game goals. Communication and high activity is required, however.

Before applying, please read the rules to make sure you can abide by them

There are no hard requirements to join and applications are handled case-to-case but here are some general things that may be taken into consideration in the process :

  • End Page History : comments, likes and action history, especially in (but not limited to) Alpha games
  • Ship outcomes : average lifespan of ships; ratio of returns to total games; ratio of assassinations to total games; presence of idle deaths, quarantines, Eden returns, assasinations by NERON; etc
  • Community reputation : forums and IRC posts, both by yourself or by others commenting on you
  • Referrals & past experiences : we may consult players who have shared ships with you

Note that these are very general items and fulfillment does not guarantee acceptance. Rejection rates are currently ~3/4 so please don't get offended personally if you are rejected

NERON

In the past, it was sometimes because applicants were already pre-engaged with a group and we didn't think they could juggle both without compromising activity for one or the other. We had a mishap with a member in two groups and we added it to our policy. This was before castings were implemented and spredsheet jumping is very different from castings since requires more setup time and coordination. Now that castings are here, we have no problem with accepting people with multiple groups.

The other most common reason is sketchy mush tactics. If we find that you were hijacking patrol ships and rampaging while achieving absolutely nothing else, then all bets are off.

Quarantines and borderline griefing reports in IRC and forums is something we look for as well, among a few other things... Sometimes, there's simply not enough information on people out there for us to make a decision.

I should add, what I'm trying to do here is ramp up the PvP and reduce drama by looking for creative mush plays and like-minded individuals less likely to be arguing over project builds and stuff.

It depends on the the casting level.
At our current level we require 24 people or more to be ready. The game checks for this every day between 0130 - 2000 Paris time. If requirements are met, [number of people]/16 (rounded down) ships are launched. The remaining people who don't get onto the ships keep their ticket. The people on the ship have characters randomly selected for them.
